Acceptance criteria

This packet is acceptable only if all of the following are true:

1. The canonical verification model is now the sole source of truth for reporting.
2. Internal format structures no longer leak into output paths.
3. Duplicate verification truth structures are materially reduced or eliminated.
4. Deterministic output is preserved.
5. The codebase now has a defensible verification-truth boundary that is difficult to accidentally bypass.
